Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n@@ -1450,8 +1450,10 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)\n \t\t} else {\n \t\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n \t\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n+\t\t\tintern->document = NULL;\n \t\t}\n \t\tintern->ptr = NULL;\n+\t\tintern->document = NULL;\n \t}\n }'}`
responded: I see! The issue is that `dom_object` is being cast to `php_libxml_node_object` at line 1449 and 1452. This means that `dom_object` and `php_libxml_node_object` have a compatible layout where the `document` field is at the same offset.

Looking at the structures:

```c
typedef struct _dom_object {
    void *ptr;
    php_libxml_ref_obj *document;  // This is the field being freed
    HashTable *prop_handler;
    zend_object std;
} dom_object;

typedef struct _php_libxml_node_object {
    php_libxml_node_ptr *node;
    php_libxml_ref_obj *document;  // This is set to NULL in php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref
    zend_object  std;
} php_libxml_node_object;
```

The issue is that when `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` is called, it sets `object->document = NULL` (line 1404 in libxml.c), but this is for the `php_libxml_node_object` structure. However, the `dom_object` structure has a different layout, so the NULL assignment might not be affecting the right field.

Let me check if there's a way to ensure that `intern->document` is also set to NULL when the document is freed. Looking at the `dom_objects_free_storage` function, I can see that it should also set `intern->document = NULL` after calling the decrement functions.

Let me create a patch that adds this:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/php_dom.c b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
index 9c3922ab5f6..43351c1d462 100644
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -1450,8 +1450,10 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)
 		} else {
 			php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
 			php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
+			intern->document = NULL;
 		}
 		intern->ptr = NULL;
+		intern->document = NULL;
 	}
 }
 /* }}} */

