responded: Now I need to understand what the issue really is. The problem seems to happen when the DOM_GET_OBJ macro is called, which might trigger some cleanup that frees the document. Let me look more carefully at the stack trace.

The stack trace shows that:
1. `dom_objects_free_storage` is called which calls `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`
2. This calls `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` which calls `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref_directly`
3. `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref_directly` frees the document at line 1383
4. But then `dom_document_save_xml` at line 1649 tries to access the freed memory

The issue is that the document can be freed during parameter parsing or DOM_GET_OBJ calls, but then the code tries to access `intern->document` later.

Looking at the failed patches, I can see that the approach was correct but incomplete. The issue is that we need to save the document reference AND ensure it stays alive during the function execution.

Let me create a proper fix. The key insight is that we need to check if the document is still valid before accessing it at line 1649:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 9650d090290..50a468d999a 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1616,6 +1616,11 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry

 	DOM_GET_OBJ(docp, ZEND_THIS, xmlDocPtr, intern);

+	/* Check if document is still valid after DOM_GET_OBJ */
+	if (!intern->document) {
+		php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document has been destroyed");
+		RETURN_FALSE;
+	}
 	libxml_doc_props const* doc_props = dom_get_doc_props_read_only(intern->document);
 	bool format = doc_props->formatoutput;

@@ -1624,6 +1629,11 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry
 		/* Dump contents of Node */
 		DOM_GET_OBJ(node, nodep, xmlNodePtr, nodeobj);
 		if (node->doc != docp) {
+			/* Check again if document is still valid after second DOM_GET_OBJ */
+			if (!intern->document) {
+				php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document has been destroyed");
+				RETURN_FALSE;
+			}
 			php_dom_throw_error(WRONG_DOCUMENT_ERR, dom_get_strict_error(intern->document));
 			RETURN_FALSE;
 		}
@@ -1632,6 +1642,11 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry
 		 * w.r.t. the implicit return in DOM_GET_OBJ). */
 		old_xml_save_no_empty_tags = xmlSaveNoEmptyTags;
 		xmlSaveNoEmptyTags = (options & LIBXML_SAVE_NOEMPTYTAG) ? 1 : 0;
+		/* Check if document is still valid before accessing handlers */
+		if (!intern->document) {
+			php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document has been destroyed");
+			RETURN_FALSE;
+		}
 		res = intern->document->handlers->dump_node_to_str(docp, node, format, (const char *) docp->encoding);
